9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 614, L.D. 949, “An Act to Clarify
10 Licensing Jurisdiction for Manufactured Housing Communities”
11 Amend the bill in section 1 in §9083 in the first indented paragraph in the 12th line
12 (page 1, line 16 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "to operate" and inserting the
13 following: 'of this subchapter'
14 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 2.
15 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 5 and inserting the following:
16 'Sec. 5. 30-A MRSA §4358, sub-§5 is enacted to read:
17 5. Fee prohibited. A municipality may not charge a fee for any type of permit for
18 manufactured housing or the installation of manufactured housing if the manufactured
19 housing or installation is governed by rules of the United States Department of Housing
20 and Urban Development or the Manufactured Housing Board.'
21 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
22 number to read consecutively.
23 SUMMARY
2244 This amendment clarifies language provided in the bill that a license issued by the
2255 Manufactured Housing Board to operate a manufactured housing community is required to
2266 be accepted by a municipality as evidence that the manufactured housing community meets
2277 the requirements of the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 10, chapter 951, subchapter 6. The
2288 amendment removes the section in the bill that allows a municipality to charge the board
2299 for inspections performed by the municipality. It also moves new language in the bill
3300 regarding certain prohibited fees to a separate subsection for clarity.
